column5: Rank (Overall rank based on Gridiron AI predicted points.)
column6: Value (How valuable a player is overall taking into account both projected points and how difficult it is to find a replacement player at their position.)
column7: Pos. Rank (Rank sorted by position and based on Gridiron AI predicted points.)
column8: Expected Points (Expected fantasy points based on the selected scoring settings.)
column9: Downside Points (Downside fantasy points based on the selected scoring settings.)
column10: Upside Points (Upside fantasy points based on the selected scoring settings.)
column11: 3-GA Points (The average points scored over the last three games excluding games where the player was inactive due to bye week, suspension, or injury.)
column12: 3-G Point Spread (The difference between max and min points in the last 3 weeks ignoring bye weeks, injuries, and suspensions. Requires the player to have been active in at least two of the last three games.)
column13: 3-GA Yards (Average sum of passing, rushing, and receiving yards over the past three weeks. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column14: 3-GA TDs (Average sum of passing, rushing, and receiving touchdowns over the past three weeks. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column15: 3-GA Turnovers (Average sum of fumbles and interceptions over the past three weeks. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column16: LG Touches (Sum of passing attempts, rushing attempts, and targets last week.)
column17: 3-GA Touches (Average sum of passing attempts, rushing attempts, and targets over the past three weeks. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column18: LG Snap % (Percent of snaps the player was on the field last week.)
column19: 3-GA Snap % (Average percent of snaps the player was on the field over the past three weeks. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column20: LG Touch % (Percent of snaps last week the player accrued a touch when they were on the field for the play.)
column21: 3-GA Touch % (Average percent of snaps over the past three weeks the player accrued a touch when they were on the field for the play. Skip BYE weeks, injuries, and suspensions.)
column22: Gridiron ID (The Gridiron AI player ID)
